<TITLE> Chidambaram India's new home minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 30 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)  Finance Minister Palaniappan Chidambaram will be India's new home (interior) minister and Prime Minister Manmohan Singh will take over the finance portfolio for now, the government said on Sunday. "As advised by the prime minister, the president has accepted the resignation of Shivraj Patil from the Ministry of Home Affairs," the government statement said. "Further as advised by the prime minister the MHA has been allocated to P. Chidambaram. The PM will himself look after ministry of finance for the time," the statement said
